andromda_persistence:FinderMethod.andromda_hibernate_query: select s from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName order by s.id
select s from StockOptionImpl as s left join fetch s.positions as p join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2 != null order by s.id
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join fetch s.components as c join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.securityFamily as f where s.isin = :isin
select s from StockOptionImpl as s join s.securityFamily as sf where sf.id = :securityFamilyId
select f from FutureImpl as f join f.securityFamily as sf where sf.id = :securityFamilyId
from OrderPreferenceImpl where securityType = :securityType and strategy.name = :strategyName

select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join p.subscriptions as su join su.strategy as st where st.name = :strategyName and s.class = :type
from StrategyImpl as st where st.name = :name
from TickImpl as t left join fetch t.security as s left join fetch s.underlying as ul left join fetch s.positions as p where t.id in (:ids) order by t.dateTime asc
select distinct c.currency from CashBalanceImpl as c left join c.strategy as s where or s.name = :strategyName
from PropertyImpl where persistent = false
select t from ImpliedVolatilityImpl as i, TickImpl as t where t.security = i and t.dateTime = :date and i.underlying = :underlying and i.duration = :duration order by i.moneyness desc
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join fetch s.components as c join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName and c2.security.class = :type and c2.quantity = 0
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2.strategy.autoActivate = true order by s.id

select t1.id from tick as t1 join (select max(id) as id from tick where date_time < :maxDate and security_fk = :securityId and time(date_time) < time(:time) group by date(date_time) ) as t2 on t1.id = t2.id order by t1.date_time asc
from FutureImpl f where f.securityFamily.id = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration = :expirationDate
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join fetch s.components as c join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName and c.security.id = :securityId
select t from TickImpl as t join t.security.subscriptions as s where s != null and t.dateTime > :startDate and t.dateTime < :endDate order by t.dateTime
from SecurityImpl as s where s.id = :id
from ForexImpl as f where f.baseCurrency = :baseCurrency and f.securityFamily.currency = :transactionCurrency
select s from StrategyImpl as s where s.autoActivate = true order by s.id
from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.underlying as ul join fetch s.securityFamily as f where s.isin = :isin
select p from com.algoTrader.entity.security.Expirable as e join e.positions as p where p.quantity != 0 and e.expiration <= :currentTime
select * from tick where security_fk = :securityId and date_time <= :maxDate order by date_time desc limit 1
from SecurityImpl as s where s.isin = :isin
select * from transaction order by date_time desc limit :maxResults

select * from ( select * from tick where security_fk = :securityId order by date_time desc limit :n
) as t order by t.date_time asc
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.components as c2 join c.subscriptions as s where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName and c2.security.class = :type
select * from tick as t where t.security_fk = :securityId and date_time <= :date and date_time > DATE_SUB(:date, INTERVAL 1 MINUTE) order by t.date_time limit 1
from FutureImpl f where f.securityFamily.id = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration >= :minExpirationDate order by f.expiration
from TickImpl as t join fetch t.security as s where t.dateTime = :date and s.underlying = :underlying and s.type = :type and s.expiration = :expiration order by s.strike
from StrategyImpl where name = :name
from ComponentImpl where persistent = false
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join fetch s.components as c join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName and c.security.class = :type
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.security.id = :securityId and p.strategy.name = :strategyName

select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join p.subscriptions as su join su.strategy as st where st.name = :strategyName and s.id = :securityId
from MeasurementImpl as m where m.strategy.name = :strategyName and m.type = :type and m.date = :date

select * from stock_option so inner join security s on s.id = so.id where s.underlying_fk = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and if(so.type = 'PUT', so.strike, -so.strike) <= if(so.type = 'PUT', :underlyingSpot, -:underlyingSpot) and so.type = :optionTypeString order by so.expiration asc, if(so.type = 'PUT', -so.strike, so.strike) asc limit 1
select p from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f left join fetch s.underlying as ul where p.id = :id
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.derivedSecurityFamilies as f where f.class = StockOptionFamilyImpl and s.id = :underlyingId
select * from future f inner join security s on s.id = f.id where s.security_family_fk = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate order by f.expiration asc limit 1
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 order by p.id

select * from stock_option so inner join security s on s.id = so.id where s.underlying_fk = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and so.type = :optionTypeString order by so.expiration asc, abs(:underlayingSpot - so.strike) asc limit 1
from TransactionImpl as t where t.type = 'CREDIT' or t.type = 'DEBIT' or t.type = 'INTREST_PAID' or t.type = 'INTREST_RECEIVED' or t.type = 'FEES' or t.type = 'REFUND' order by t.id
select s from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2 != null and f.periodicity = :periodicity order by s.id
from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.underlying as ul join fetch s.securityFamily as f where s.id = :id
select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join p.subscriptions as su join su.strategy as st where st.name = :strategyName
select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join s.subscriptions as su where su != null and s.id = :securityId
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2 != null order by s.id
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 and s.class = ForexImpl order by p.id
from SubscriptionImpl as s where s.strategy.autoActivate = true and s.security.id = :securityId order by s.id
select p from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.quantity != 0 order by p.id

select t1.id from tick as t1 join (select min(id) as id from tick where date_time < :maxDate and security_fk = :securityId and time(date_time) > time(:time) group by date(date_time) ) as t2 on t1.id = t2.id order by t1.date_time asc
select distinct dateTime from TickImpl
from SecurityImpl as s where s.symbol = :symbol
from SubscriptionImpl where persistent = true
select distinct s.expiration from TickImpl as t join t.security as s where t.dateTime = :dateTime and s.class = StockOptionImpl and s.underlying.id = :underlyingId order by s.expiration
select distinct c.currency from CashBalanceImpl as c
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.strategy.name = :strategyName order by p.id

select s2 from SubscriptionImpl as s2 join s2.security as s where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName and s not in ( select p.security from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0) and s.class = :type
select * from transaction as t join strategy as s on s.id = t.strategy_fk where s.name = :strategyName order by t.date_time desc limit :maxResults
from TickImpl as s where s.security.id = :securityId order by s.dateTime
from SecurityImpl as s where s.id in (:ids) order by s.id
select t.id from ( select * from tick where security_fk = :securityId order by date_time desc limit :n ) as t order by t.date_time asc
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.security.id = :securityId and p.quantity != 0 order by p.id
from SubscriptionImpl where strategy.name = :strategyName order by security.id
from MeasurementImpl as m where m.strategy.name = :strategyName and m.type = :type and m.date > :date order by m.date
from CombinationImpl where persistent = false
from SubscriptionImpl where persistent = false

select s.*, so.* from stock_option so inner join security s on s.id = so.id join tick as t on s.id = t.security_fk where s.underlying_fk = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and so.type = :optionTypeString and t.date_time = :date order by so.expiration asc, abs(:underlayingSpot - so.strike) asc limit 1
from SubscriptionImpl as s where s.strategy.name = :strategyName and s.security not in ( select p.security from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0)

select s.*, so.* from stock_option so inner join security s on s.id = so.id join tick as t on s.id = t.security_fk where s.underlying_fk = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and if(so.type = 'PUT', so.strike, -so.strike) <= if(so.type = 'PUT', :underlyingSpot, -:underlyingSpot) and so.type = :optionTypeString and t.date_time = :date order by so.expiration asc, if(so.type = 'PUT', -so.strike, so.strike) asc limit 1
from TransactionImpl as t join fetch t.security where t.type = 'BUY' or t.type = 'SELL' or t.type = 'EXPIRATION' order by t.id
select f from FutureImpl as f left join fetch f.positions as p join f.subscriptions as s where s != null order by f.id
select p from PositionImpl as p where p.id = :id
from SubscriptionImpl where strategy.name = :strategyName and security.id = :securityId
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.derivedSecurityFamilies as f where f.class = FutureFamilyImpl and s.id = :underlyingId
select p from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.quantity != 0 and s.class = ForexImpl order by p.id
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.underlying as ul join fetch c.components as c2 join c.subscriptions as s3 where s3.strategy.name = :strategyName and ul.id = :underlyingId
